Online Quiz Management System using SpringBoot ( Folder named as Assignment )

Project Overview:
The Online Quiz Management System allows users to participate in quizzes with multiple questions. Each quiz consists of multiple questions, and the system supports functionalities like creating quizzes, adding questions, and retrieving quiz details.

Entities and Relationships:
Questions Model: Represents individual quiz questions, including fields like id, questionText, options, and correctAnswer.
Quiz Model: Represents a quiz that groups multiple questions. Contains fields like id, title, description, and a list of associated questions.
Mapping: A One-to-Many relationship is established, where a quiz can have multiple questions.

Key Functionalities:
Create Quiz: Add a quiz with multiple questions.
Retrieve Quiz Details: Fetch quizzes along with their associated questions.
Evaluate Quiz: Allow users to submit answers and receive scores.
Admin Panel: Manage questions and quizzes.



Technologies Used:
Backend: Spring Boot, Spring Data JPA, Hibernate.
Database: MySQL.
Testing: Postman for API testing.
Dependencies: Spring Boot Starter Web, Spring Boot Starter JPA/ Mysql connector.


To-Do List Web Application (Spring Boot Project)
Developed a To-Do List Web Application using Spring Boot, designed to manage tasks efficiently with CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) functionality.
Key Features:
User Authentication: Secure login and registration system.
Task Management: Add, edit, mark as complete, and delete tasks.
Categorization: Organize tasks by priority and due dates.
RESTful API Integration: Exposed endpoints for task management.
Database Handling: Used Hibernate with MySQL for data persistence.
Front-end Integration: Integrated with Thymeleaf and Bootstrap for a user-friendly interface.
Tech Stack:
Backend: Spring Boot, Spring MVC, Spring Data JPA
Frontend: HTML, CSS, Bootstrap, Thymeleaf
Database: MySQL
Version Control: GitHub
Outcome:
Enhanced productivity by providing users with a simple and intuitive platform to manage daily tasks effectively.
